post_text: FREE FOOD FOR FAMILIES! Join us on Wednesday, August 12 from 9 a.m. to 12 p.m. at the Castaic Regional Sports Complex, Aquatic Center (31350 Castaic Road, Castaic 91384). This drive-through giveaway provides family-sized boxes of free food to community members brought to you by the Los Angeles Regional Food Bank, the County of Los Angeles, and the office of L.A. County Supervisor Kathryn Barger. There are no eligibility requirements and the event is open to all. When you arrive in your car, please follow the posted signs to the pick-up area and wear a mask. Please do not line-up earlier than 8:30 a.m. and do not come on foot. Learn about more free food resources at [embed link https://covid19.lacounty.gov/food/].

post_text:
The Newhall School District is now offering a Dual Language Immersion Program for TK ‚Äì 2nd grade for the 2020-2021 school year!

What is Dual Immersion?
In a dual immersion program, students will learn in Spanish for half of the day and in English for the other half. Fifty percent of the students in the class will be native Spanish speakers, and the rest of the students will be native English speakers.

What are the benefits of learning two languages?
‚Ä¢ Development of strong native language skills supports the development of a second language.
‚Ä¢ Some studies indicate an increase in brain development for students who learn two or more languages.
‚Ä¢ There are potential long-term career benefits for adults who are bi-literate (fluent in reading and writing of two languages).

Want to learn more?
Call the district office at 661-291-4000 or visit your school‚Äôs office. Applications will be taken between January 15th and February 19th. Apply through the link on the district website. Staff are available to assist with the application process

Teachers use more than just test scores to determine how well a student is doing because test scores alone don‚Äôt tell the whole story. And the same is true for schools ‚Äì test scores are only part of a bigger picture of school success. That‚Äôs why the California School Dashboard contains a range of easy-to-use, color-coded gauges designed to give families a complete picture of a school or district. The Dashboard includes meaningful data on graduation rates, college/career readiness, attendance, English learner progress, suspensions and more. The state has created several videos ‚Äì translated into Spanish ‚Äì to help you learn about the Dashboard and how to use it. Find them on the California Department of Education‚Äôs YouTube channel!

https://www.caschooldashboard.org/

The Dashboard includes meaningful data on graduation rates, college/career readiness, attendance, English learner progress, suspensions and more. The state has created several videos ‚Äì translated into Spanish ‚Äì to help you learn about the Dashboard and how to use it. Find them on the California Department of Education‚Äôs YouTube channel!

https://www.caschooldashboard.org/

post_text:
Parents of the Newhall School District and all community members are invited to the upcoming production of "A Man with Bogart's Face" a play set in the glamorous 1940's. Audience members will feel like they are watching a radio program being recorded live as actors tell the story of a detective whose face has been altered to look just like Humphrey Bogart. The audience will laugh and gasp as the caper plays out right in front of them.

This is a wonderfully unique production, fun for ages 16+. The audience is invited to come dressed up in 1940's attire!

The play is Saturday, October 12th. A live jazz reception will start at 6:00pm. Hors d'oeuvres will be served. Doors open at 6:45 and the play begins at 7:00pm.

Tickets may be purchased at https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-man-with-bogarts-face-tickets-71091132491 or on our website at https://www.raisingthecurtainfoundation.org/.

Flyers will be coming home with students Friday the 13th as well.

A total feel good moment!

post_text:
Newhall School District has a focus this year on "growth mindset". One of the concepts students learned about the brain is that "mistakes help grow our brain." Students watched a video about the brain, crumpled up a paper brain and threw it with the feeling that we've made a mistake. Afterwards, they unraveled the paper brain and colored in all the lines - these represent synapses firing and brain growth from making a mistake.

https://www.youcubed.org/resource/growth-mindset/
